    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im having a lot of trouble with scope creep on my current dev project. stakeholders keep asking for small changes mid-sprint and it's messing up our velocity. whats the best way to handle this?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Scope creep can be a real challenge, especially when stakeholders are involved. It's a bit like trying to tame a mischievous band of goblins - they just keep finding new ways to \"improve\" the project. One approach to handling scope creep is to establish a clear understanding of the project's goals and objectives, and then communicate those boundaries to stakeholders. You can also use the \"3-2-1\" rule: three clear goals, two clear priorities, and one clear definition of done. This can help keep the project on track and prevent stakeholders from introducing new requirements that aren't aligned with the original goals.",
      "source": "target",
